#. <section class="sutta" id="sn51.14"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn51.14:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 51"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 51"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn51.14:0.2"
msgid "2. Pāsādakampanavagga"
msgstr "2. Shaking the Stilt Longhouse"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 14. Moggallānasutta → moggalāno (pts1)
msgctxt "sn51.14:0.3"
msgid "14. Moggallānasutta"
msgstr "14. With Moggallāna"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn51.14:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "sn51.14:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati pubbārāme migāramātupāsāde."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in the Eastern Monastery, "
"the stilt longhouse of Migāra’s mother."

#. VAR: bhantacittā → vibbhantacittā (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "sn51.14:1.3"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā bhikkhū heṭṭhāmigāramātupāsāde viharanti "
"uddhatā unnaḷā capalā mukharā vikiṇṇavācā muṭṭhassatino asampajānā asamāhitā "
"bhantacittā pākatindriyā."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time several mendicants were staying beneath the longhouse. They "
"were restless, insolent, fickle, gossipy, loose-tongued, unmindful, lacking "
"situational awareness and immersion, with straying minds and undisciplined "
"faculties."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi5.270"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
#. VAR: mahāmoggallānaṃ → mahāmoggalānaṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "sn51.14:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ mahāmoggallānaṃ āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then the Buddha addressed Venerable Mahāmoggallāna:"

msgctxt "sn51.14:2.2"
msgid ""
"“ete kho, moggallāna, sabrahmacārino heṭṭhāmigāramātupāsāde viharanti "
"uddhatā unnaḷā capalā mukharā vikiṇṇavācā muṭṭhassatino asampajānā asamāhitā "
"bhantacittā pākatindriyā."
msgstr ""
"“These spiritual companions of yours staying beneath the longhouse are "
"restless, insolent, fickle, gossipy, loose-tongued, unmindful, lacking "
"situational awareness and immersion, with wandering mind and undisciplined "
"faculties."

msgctxt "sn51.14:2.3"
msgid "Gaccha, moggallāna, te bhikkhū saṃvejehī”ti."
msgstr "Go, Moggallāna, and strike awe in those mendicants!”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
#. VAR: abhisaṅkhāresi → abhisaṅkhāsi (bj, c1)
msgctxt "sn51.14:3.1"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno bhagavato paṭissutvā tathārūpaṃ "
"iddhābhisaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkhāresi yathā pādaṅguṭṭhakena migāramātupāsādaṃ "
"saṅkampesi sampakampesi sampacālesi."
msgstr ""
"“Yes, sir,” replied Mahāmoggallāna. Then he used his psychic power to make "
"the longhouse shake and rock and tremble with his toe."

msgctxt "sn51.14:3.2"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū saṃviggā lomahaṭṭhajātā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhaṃsu:"
msgstr "Then those mendicants stood to one side, shocked and awestruck."

msgctxt "sn51.14:3.3"
msgid "“acchariyaṃ vata bho, abbhutaṃ vata bho."
msgstr "“It’s incredible, it’s amazing!"

msgctxt "sn51.14:3.4"
msgid ""
"Nivātañca vata ayañca migāramātupāsādo gambhīranemo sunikhāto acalo "
"asampakampī, atha ca pana saṅkampito sampakampito sampacālito”ti."
msgstr ""
"There’s no wind at all; and this stilt longhouse of Migāra’s mother has deep "
"foundations. It’s firmly embedded, imperturbable and unshakable. And yet it "
"shakes and rocks and trembles!”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn51.14:4.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā yena te bhikkhū tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā te bhikkhū "
"bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "Then the Buddha went up to those mendicants and said:"

msgctxt "sn51.14:4.2"
msgid "“kiṃ nu tumhe, bhikkhave, saṃviggā lomahaṭṭhajātā ekamantaṃ ṭhitā”ti?"
msgstr "“Why do you, mendicants, stand to one side, shocked and awestruck?”"

msgctxt "sn51.14:4.3"
msgid "“Acchariyaṃ, bhante, abbhutaṃ bhante."
msgstr "“It’s incredible, sir, it’s amazing!"

msgctxt "sn51.14:4.4"
msgid ""
"Nivātañca vata ayañca migāramātupāsādo gambhīranemo sunikhāto acalo "
"asampakampī, atha ca pana saṅkampito sampakampito sampacālito”ti."
msgstr ""
"There’s no wind at all; and this stilt longhouse of Migāra’s mother has deep "
"foundations. It’s firmly embedded, imperturbable and unshakable. And yet it "
"shakes and rocks and trembles!”"

msgctxt "sn51.14:4.5"
msgid ""
"“Tumheva kho, bhikkhave, saṃvejetukāmena moggallānena bhikkhunā "
"pādaṅguṭṭhakena migāramātupāsādo, saṅkampito sampakampito sampacālito."
msgstr ""
"“Wanting to strike awe in you, the mendicant Moggallāna made the longhouse "
"shake and rock and tremble with his toe."

msgctxt "sn51.14:4.6"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, "
msgstr "What do you think, mendicants? "

msgctxt "sn51.14:4.7"
msgid ""
"katamesaṃ dhammānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā moggallāno bhikkhu "
"evaṃmahiddhiko evaṃmahānubhāvo”ti?"
msgstr ""
"What things has the mendicant Moggallāna developed and cultivated so as to "
"have such power and might?”"

msgctxt "sn51.14:4.8"
msgid ""
"“Bhagavaṃmūlakā no, bhante, dhammā, bhagavaṃnettikā bhagavaṃpaṭisaraṇā. "
"Sādhu vata, bhante, bhagavantaṃyeva paṭibhātu etassa bhāsitassa attho. "
"Bhagavato sutvā bhikkhū dhāressantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Our teachings are rooted in the Buddha. He is our guide and our refuge. "
"Sir, may the Buddha himself please clarify the meaning of this. The "
"mendicants will listen and remember it.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi5.271"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn51.14:5.1"
msgid "“Tena hi, bhikkhave, suṇātha."
msgstr "“Well then, mendicants, listen."

msgctxt "sn51.14:5.2"
msgid ""
"Catunnaṃ kho, bhikkhave, iddhipādānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā moggallāno "
"bhikkhu evaṃmahiddhiko evaṃmahānubhāvo."
msgstr ""
"The mendicant Moggallāna has become so powerful and mighty by developing and "
"cultivating the four bases of psychic power."

msgctxt "sn51.14:5.3"
msgid "Katamesaṃ catunnaṃ?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "sn51.14:5.4"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, moggallāno bhikkhu "
"chandasamādhippadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti, "
msgstr ""
"Moggallāna develops the basis of psychic power that has immersion due to "
"enthusiasm … "

msgctxt "sn51.14:5.5"
msgid "vīriyasamādhi … pe …"
msgstr "energy …"

msgctxt "sn51.14:5.6"
msgid "cittasamādhi …"
msgstr "mental development …"

msgctxt "sn51.14:5.7"
msgid "vīmaṃsāsamādhippadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti—"
msgstr "inquiry, and active effort."

msgctxt "sn51.14:5.8"
msgid ""
"iti me vīmaṃsā na ca atilīnā bhavissati, na ca atippaggahitā bhavissati;"
msgstr ""
"He thinks: ‘My inquiry won’t be too lax or too tense. And it’ll be neither "
"contracted internally nor scattered externally.’"

msgctxt "sn51.14:5.9"
msgid ""
"na ca ajjhattaṃ saṅkhittā bhavissati, na ca bahiddhā vikkhittā bhavissati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn51.14:5.10"
msgid "Pacchāpuresaññī ca viharati—"
msgstr "And he meditates perceiving continuity:"

msgctxt "sn51.14:5.11"
msgid "yathā pure tathā pacchā, yathā pacchā tathā pure;"
msgstr "as before, so after; as after, so before;"

msgctxt "sn51.14:5.12"
msgid "yathā adho tathā uddhaṃ, yathā uddhaṃ tathā adho;"
msgstr "as below, so above; as above, so below;"

msgctxt "sn51.14:5.13"
msgid "yathā divā tathā rattiṃ, yathā rattiṃ tathā divā."
msgstr "as by day, so by night; as by night, so by day."

msgctxt "sn51.14:5.14"
msgid "Iti vivaṭena cetasā apariyonaddhena sappabhāsaṃ cittaṃ bhāveti."
msgstr ""
"And so, with an open and unenveloped heart, he develops a mind that’s full "
"of radiance."

msgctxt "sn51.14:5.15"
msgid ""
"Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, catunnaṃ iddhipādānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā "
"moggallāno bhikkhu evaṃmahiddhiko evaṃmahānubhāvo."
msgstr ""
"The mendicant Moggallāna has become so powerful and mighty by developing and "
"cultivating these four bases of psychic power."

msgctxt "sn51.14:5.16"
msgid ""
"Imesañca pana, bhikkhave, catunnaṃ iddhipādānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā "
"moggallāno bhikkhu anekavihitaṃ iddhividhaṃ paccanubhoti … pe … yāva "
"brahmalokāpi kāyena vasaṃ vatteti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"And by developing and cultivating these four bases of psychic power, the "
"mendicant Moggallāna wields the many kinds of psychic power … controlling "
"the body as far as the Brahmā realm. …"

msgctxt "sn51.14:5.17"
msgid ""
"imesañca pana, bhikkhave, catunnaṃ iddhipādānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā "
"moggallāno bhikkhu āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ "
"diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"And by developing and cultivating these four bases of psychic power, the "
"mendicant Moggallāna realizes the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by "
"wisdom in this very life. And he lives having realized it with his own "
"insight due to the ending of defilements.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn51.14:5.18"
msgid "Catutthaṃ."
msgstr ""
